WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.674 --> 00:00:18.223
The first time I uttered a prayer was in a glass-stained cathedral.
我第一次的祈祷是在装饰着彩色玻璃教堂。

2
00:00:18.223 --> 00:00:21.613
I was kneeling long after the congregation was on its feet,
会众起身，我长久地跪着

3
00:00:21.613 --> 00:00:23.523
dip both hands into holy water,
将双手沁入圣水中，

4
00:00:23.523 --> 00:00:25.373
trace the trinity across my chest,
在胸前划着十字，

5
00:00:25.373 --> 00:00:28.199
my tiny body drooping like a question mark
我瘦小的身体低垂如同一个问号

6
00:00:28.199 --> 00:00:30.489
all over the wooden pew.
在木制的长椅上。

7
00:00:30.489 --> 00:00:33.159
I asked Jesus to fix me,
我请上帝解救我，

8
00:00:33.159 --> 00:00:35.285
and when he did not answer
当他没有回答

9
00:00:35.285 --> 00:00:37.961
I befriended silence in the hopes that my sin would burn
我与寂静为友希望我的罪恶燃烧

10
00:00:37.961 --> 00:00:39.451
and salve my mouth
我的嘴巴会溶解

11
00:00:39.451 --> 00:00:41.281
would dissolve like sugar on tongue,
就像舌头上的糖，

12
00:00:41.281 --> 00:00:43.196
but shame lingered as an aftertaste.
但是羞耻如同后味般徘徊。

13
00:00:43.196 --> 00:00:46.760
And in an attempt to reintroduce me to sanctity,
在试图重回神圣，

14
00:00:46.760 --> 00:00:49.680
my mother told me of the miracle I was,
我母亲告诉我，我是个奇迹

15
00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:52.680
said I could grow up to be anything I want.
她说我可以成为我想成为的人。

16
00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:54.886
I decided to
于是我决定

17
00:00:54.886 --> 00:00:56.047
be a boy.
成为一个男孩。

18
00:00:56.047 --> 00:00:57.037
It was cute.
这太可爱了。

19
00:00:57.037 --> 00:00:58.827
I had snapback, toothless grin,
我有快速、没牙的笑容，

20
00:00:58.827 --> 00:01:00.667
used skinned knees as street cred,
以脱皮的膝盖作为街头信誉，

21
00:01:00.667 --> 00:01:03.097
played hide and seek with what was left of my goal.
用我所剩下的目标去玩捉迷藏。

22
00:01:03.097 --> 00:01:04.024
I was it.
我曾是这样。

23
00:01:04.024 --> 00:01:06.449
The winner to a game the other kids couldn't play,
我是游戏赢家其它孩子无法加入这场游戏，

24
00:01:06.449 --> 00:01:08.629
I was the mystery of an anatomy,
我是解剖学的奇迹，

25
00:01:08.629 --> 00:01:10.442
a question asked but not answered,
一个被提出了却又无解的问题，

26
00:01:10.442 --> 00:01:14.738
tightroping between awkward boy and apologetic girl,
我在举止奇怪的男孩和谦虚的女孩间徘徊，

27
00:01:14.738 --> 00:01:19.475
and when I turned 12, the boy phase wasn't deemed cute anymore.
当我12岁的时候，男孩的阶段不再可爱。

28
00:01:19.475 --> 00:01:25.117
It was met with nostalgic aunts who missed seeing my knees in the shadow of skirts,
怀旧的姑妈想念我裙摆下的膝盖，

29
00:01:25.117 --> 00:01:29.366
who reminded me that my kind of attitude would never bring a husband home,
告诉我，以我这样的态度是不会找到丈夫的，

30
00:01:29.366 --> 00:01:32.988
that I exist for heterosexual marriage and child-bearing.
我的存在是为了异性婚姻和生孩子。

31
00:01:32.988 --> 00:01:36.819
And I swallowed their insults along with their slurs.
我忍耐、吞下他们的侮辱和诽谤。

32
00:01:36.819 --> 00:01:39.536
Naturally, I did not come out of the closet.
自然地，我没有出柜。

33
00:01:39.536 --> 00:01:42.252
The kids at my school opened it without my permission.
我同校的孩子们未经我允许打开了这个柜子。

34
00:01:42.252 --> 00:01:44.714
Called me by a name I did not recognize,
给了我一个我不要的名字

35
00:01:44.714 --> 00:01:45.944
said "lesbian,"
“蕾丝边” 女同性恋者，

36
00:01:45.944 --> 00:01:48.520
but I was more boy than girl, more Ken than Barbie.
我比起女孩更像男孩，我更像是肯而不是芭比。

37
00:01:48.520 --> 00:01:50.723
It had nothing to do with hating my body,
无关憎恨我的身体，

38
00:01:50.723 --> 00:01:52.843
I just love it enough to let it go,
我让它离开是因为太爱它了，

39
00:01:52.843 --> 00:01:54.229
I treat it like a house,
我把身体当做一个房子，

40
00:01:54.229 --> 00:01:56.059
and when your house is falling apart,
当你的房子崩坏倒塌，

41
00:01:56.059 --> 00:01:57.043
you do not evacuate,
你不会撤离，

42
00:01:57.043 --> 00:02:00.835
you make it comfortable enough to house all your insides,
你会把它变成足够舒适能承载你的所有，

43
00:02:00.835 --> 00:02:03.196
you make it pretty enough to invite guests over,
你会把它变得足够漂亮能邀请人们做客，

44
00:02:03.196 --> 00:02:07.054
you make the floorboards strong enough to stand on.
你会让地板变得坚硬能够平稳站立。

45
00:02:07.724 --> 00:02:12.739
My mother fears I have named myself after fading things.
我的母亲害怕我以凋谢的事物命名自己。

46
00:02:12.739 --> 00:02:15.759
As she counts the echoes left behind by Mya Hall,
她数着那些名字和其身后的回响米娅·霍尔，

47
00:02:15.759 --> 00:02:18.309
Leelah Alcorn, Blake Brockington.
莉拉·奥尔康，布莱克·布鲁金顿。

48
00:02:18.309 --> 00:02:20.520
She fears that I'll die without a whisper,
她害怕我会默默死去，

49
00:02:20.520 --> 00:02:23.583
that I'll turn into "what a shame" conversations at the bus stop.
我会变成巴士站闲谈人们口中的“太遗憾了。”

50
00:02:23.583 --> 00:02:26.229
She claims I have turned myself into a mausoleum,
她说我已经把自己变成了陵墓，

51
00:02:26.229 --> 00:02:27.855
that I am a walking casket,
我是一个移动的棺材，

52
00:02:27.855 --> 00:02:31.059
news headlines have turned my identity into a spectacle,
新闻头条把我的身份变成了人间奇观，

53
00:02:31.059 --> 00:02:34.815
Bruce Jenner on everyone's lips while the brutality of living in this body
布鲁斯·詹娜是人们的谈资然而无情生活在他的身体里

54
00:02:34.815 --> 00:02:38.361
becomes an asterisk  at the bottom of equality pages.
变成平等页面下面的星标。

55
00:02:38.361 --> 00:02:41.457
No one ever thinks of us as human
没人甚至将我们视为人类

56
00:02:41.457 --> 00:02:43.615
because we are more ghost than flesh,
因为比起活着的人，我们更像鬼，

57
00:02:43.615 --> 00:02:46.314
because people fear that my gender expression is a trick,
人们害怕我的性别像是一个诡计，

58
00:02:46.314 --> 00:02:48.171
that it exists to be perverse,
那是违反常情的，

59
00:02:48.171 --> 00:02:50.214
that it ensnares them without their consent,
未经同意就将他们诱捕入网，

60
00:02:50.214 --> 00:02:52.908
that my body is a feast for their eyes and hands
对他们的眼睛和手而言我的身体是一场盛宴

61
00:02:52.908 --> 00:02:55.207
and once they have fed off my queer,
直到他们受够了我同性恋的古怪，

62
00:02:55.207 --> 00:02:58.207
they'll regurgitate all the parts they did not like.
他们会吐出那些他们不喜欢的部分。

63
00:02:58.207 --> 00:03:02.567
They'll put me back into the closet, hang me with all the other skeletons.
他们会把我放回衣柜和其他的骨骼挂在一起。

64
00:03:02.567 --> 00:03:04.982
I will be the best attraction.
我会成为最受欢迎的奇观。

65
00:03:04.982 --> 00:03:08.061
Can you see how easy it is to talk people into coffins,
可以看见吗？要把人们说进棺材是多么容易的事情，

66
00:03:08.061 --> 00:03:10.631
to misspell their names on gravestones.
在墓碑上错误拼写他们的名字。

67
00:03:10.631 --> 00:03:13.086
And people still wonder why there are boys rotting,
人们仍在寻思为什么男孩们腐烂，

68
00:03:13.086 --> 00:03:15.477
they go away in high school hallways
他们走进高中的走廊

69
00:03:15.477 --> 00:03:18.379
they are afraid of becoming another hashtag in a second
他们担心某一秒突然变成标签

70
00:03:18.379 --> 00:03:22.257
afraid of classroom discussions becoming like judgment day
害怕同学们的谈论变成他们的审判日

71
00:03:22.257 --> 00:03:27.992
and now oncoming traffic is embracing more transgender children than parents.
现在，更多陌生人开始拥抱变性孩童比他们的父母还要容易接受。

72
00:03:28.882 --> 00:03:30.627
I wonder how long it will be
我不知道这要多久

73
00:03:30.627 --> 00:03:34.307
before the trans suicide notes start to feel redundant,
直到自杀留言开始变得多余，

74
00:03:34.307 --> 00:03:37.930
before we realize that our bodies become lessons about sin
直到我们意识到自己的身体成为罪恶的教科书

75
00:03:37.930 --> 00:03:39.973
way before we learn how to love them.
早于我们了解如何爱自己的身体。

76
00:03:39.973 --> 00:03:43.897
Like God didn't save all this breath and mercy,
就像上帝并未存有这些气息和宽容，

77
00:03:43.897 --> 00:03:47.473
like my blood is not the wine that washed over Jesus' feet.
就像我的血液不是泼在耶稣脚上的葡萄酒。

78
00:03:47.473 --> 00:03:51.341
My prayers are now getting stuck in my throat.
我的祷告卡在喉咙。

79
00:03:51.861 --> 00:03:54.995
Maybe I am finally fixed,
也许我终于被解救，

80
00:03:54.995 --> 00:03:57.248
maybe I just don't care,
也许我就是不在乎，

81
00:03:57.248 --> 00:04:01.959
maybe God finally listened to my prayers.
也许上帝终于听到我的祷告。

82
00:04:01.959 --> 00:04:03.424
Thank you.
谢谢。

83
00:04:03.424 --> 00:04:05.528
(Applause)
（鼓掌）